message: The Democratic Party of JFK is very nearly dead and buried and there are next-to-no blue-collar JFK Democrats left. The Democratic Party is now extreme-left Progressive/Socialist. Joe Leiberman was one of the last few JFK-style Democrats left and just look what the Democratic Party did to him! They so attacked and vilified him that he had to leave the Party. Jim Webb is also one of those blue-collar JFK-style Democrats and may even be the last true JFK-style Democrat leader standing. Most Democrats that I speak to are under the impression that the Democratic Party is still """"the party of JFK"""" and that is just patently untrue. The Democrat rank-and-file REALLY need to look a lot more closely at just exactly who they are associated with and supporting.

Well...I am sure there are many different attitudes among fishermen. Overfishing of so many species argues against care for the oceans as being universal, as does the massive amount of netting killing wildlife. Sometimes the question is not whether or not people care, but if they care enough to do the right thing. My sense is that the family farm vs agribusiness analogy works here. Massive nets that sweep up every living thing are not left by small family businesses. And it is also true that some family farms set the standard for humane and environmentally sensitive farming, while other farmers are all about the bottom line and maximizing profits.
